# Plan Mode First

Use plan mode (read-only, plan-then-confirm) before any change that meets ANY of:

1. Touches >2 files
2. Touches a danger zone (see `protected-regions.mdc`)
3. Adds a new model, route, or Celery task
4. Modifies billing, auth, multi-tenancy, or risk gate code
5. Modifies indicator math (anything in `apis/axiomfolio/app/services/market/indicator_engine.py`)
6. Refactors a module that other modules import from

## Why

The 4-month v0 incident pattern (D76-D80, R34-R39) was largely "well-intentioned edit lacked context, broke prod". A 60-second plan-mode check would have caught most of them.

## What goes in a plan

- Files to be modified (full paths) and what changes in each
- New files with one-sentence purpose
- Schema changes (model + Alembic migration) if any
- Test additions if any
- Acceptance criteria — what does success look like?
- Reversibility — can this be reverted cleanly?
- Reference to related KNOWLEDGE.md entry if architectural

## When plan mode is NOT needed

- Single-file typo fix
- Adding a comment
- Updating one log message
- Editing a doc file
- Renaming an unused variable

## Master plan reference

For multi-PR sprint work, link your plan to the relevant phase in `docs/plans/MASTER_PLAN_2026.md`. Don't invent new milestones; use what's there.
